Learning Outcome: Evaluate applications of data science to real-world problems

Societies feel like a hot mess these days. We want to build inclusive, fair systems,
but how can we do that effectively? Data can inform decision-making in important ways that are both transparent and transformative.

What societal grand challenge would you want to tackle using data? Where would you find the data? This can be data that you think might already exist or you can offer
a creative solution for collecting data that doesn't exist yet.

Your post should be around 6-8 sentences long with a clear topic sentence at the beginning of each paragraph.

Please add citations of lecture material (or from outside sources) to add a broader expertise and knowledge base to your argument.

Remember to comment on 2 other posts in a meaningful and helpful way to encourage more discussion.